%20Bhattacharji.%20Publisher%3A%20Harper%20Collins%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20new%20book%20by%20Romesh%20Bhattacharji%20(%3Cem%3EKashmir%20%E2%80%93%20Travels%20in%20Paradise%20on%20Earth%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20Harper%20Collins)%20has%20shined%20a%20broad%20and%20bright%20spotlight%20on%20this%20scenic%20and%20unspoilt%20landscape%20of%20Kashmir%2C%20and%20the%20countless%20possibilities%20it%20offers%20for%20nature%20lovers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20book%20is%20an%20impressive%20achievement%20because%20it%20is%20perhaps%20a%20first-of-its-kind%20comprehensive%20guide%20on%20the%20easy%2C%20moderate%20and%20difficult%20mountain%20traverses%20along%20the%20complete%20portion%20of%20the%20Himalaya%20and%20Pir%20Panjal%20range%20surrounding%20Kashmir.%20Bhattacharji%20confesses%20that%20he%20has%20not%20hit%20them%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20such%20trail%20skirts%20two%20splendid%20alpine%20lakes%20in%20the%20upper%20reaches%20of%20Sonamarg%20to%20approach%20the%20difficult%20Lakhath%20gali%20(4375m).%20It%20is%20a%20heady%20trail%20which%20was%20taken%20by%20Ernest%20Neve%20and%20Kenneth%20Mason%20to%20make%20the%20first%20ascent%20of%20Mt%20Kolahoi%20(5425m)%2C%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20second%20highest%20peak%2C%20in%201912.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20hundred%20and%20ten%20years%20later%2C%20on%20a%20cold%20September%20morning%20in%202022%2C%20Gulzar%20Ahmed%2C%20a%20man%20of%20mountains%20and%20our%20guide%2C%20I%20and%20Riyaz%20Lone%20(of%20Kashmir%20Hikes)%20woke%20up%20near%20the%20steep%2C%20scree-filled%20slopes%20of%20Lakhath%C2%A0%3Ci%3Egali%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0in%20a%20half-pitched%20tent%20strung%20to%20mountain%20boulders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20difficult%20night%2C%20we%20were%20truly%20fortunate%20and%20blessed%20by%20the%20sight%20of%20the%20first%20golden%20rays%20of%20sun%20embracing%20the%20northern%20face%20of%20Mt%20Kolahoi%20which%20resembled%20a%20sleeping%20Buddha.%20It%20was%20a%20truly%20jaw-dropping%20moment%20which%20every%20mountain%20lover%20should%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhattacharji%E2%80%99s%20book%20is%20divided%20into%2021%20easy%20chapters%20which%20speak%20admiringly%20about%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccharm%20of%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20nooks%20and%20crannies%2C%20the%20splendour%20of%20its%20lakes%20and%20meadows%2C%20and%20the%20beauty%20of%20its%20valleys%20and%20peaks%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20these%2C%2018%20chapters%20list%20out%20meticulous%20details%20about%20the%20endless%20trails%20skirting%20up%20and%20down%20a%20range%20of%20%E2%80%9Cfriendly%20mountains%E2%80%9D%20which%20are%20studded%20with%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnecklace%20of%20extravagantly%20beautiful%E2%80%9D%20oligotrophic%20lakes%20and%20tarns.%20As%20the%20author%20points%20out%2C%20some%20of%20these%20nature%E2%80%99s%20wonders%20are%20only%20a%20day%E2%80%99s%20hike%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F09104614%2FIMG_5904.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F09104614%2FIMG_5904.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F09104614%2FIMG_5904-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F09104614%2FIMG_5904-1024x768.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-700882%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20imposing%20northern%20face%20of%20Mt%20Kolahoi%20seen%20from%20the%20difficult%20Lakhath%20gali%20which%20sits%20at%20the%20confluence%20of%20Sindh%20and%20Lidder%20valleys%20in%20the%20upper%20reaches%20of%20Sonamarg.%20Photo%3A%20Jehangir%20Ali%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20book%20begins%20across%20the%20Banihal%C2%A0%3Ci%3Egali%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0where%20the%20new%20railway%20line%20and%20the%20old%20national%20highway%20burst%20into%20Kashmir%20through%20the%20Pir%20Panjal%20mountain%20range.%20Down%20on%20the%20right%20side%20of%20the%20highway%20is%20Verinag%2C%20a%20jewel%20of%20a%20massive%20spring%20set%20in%20an%20octagon%20of%20sculpted%20stones.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20hike%20to%20Halan%20gali%20from%20Verinag%20and%20beyond%20offers%20stunning%20views%20of%20the%20Himalayas%20including%20the%20Nichang%20(5444m)%2C%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20highest%20peak%2C%20and%20Kolahoi%20or%C2%A0%3Ci%3EGwashe%20Bor%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3Erunning%20west%20from%20the%20Great%20Himalayan%20Crest%2C%20and%20the%20distant%20Nun-Kun%20massif%20in%20Ladakh%20among%20other%20Himalayan%20alps.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUsing%20Verinag%20as%20a%20starting%20point%2C%20Bhattacharji%20takes%20the%20reader%20on%20the%20complete%20traverse%20of%20mountains%20circling%20the%20Kashmir%20Valley%20which%20has%20%E2%80%9Cso%20much%20grandeur%20in%20every%20square%20mile%E2%80%9D%20with%20nearly%20every%20village%20serving%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbase%20for%20memorable%20walks%20to%20meadows%20and%20tarns%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20242-page%20book%20has%20a%20lovely%2C%20turquoise-coloured%20Gangbal%20lake%20seen%20from%20the%20Gadsar%20pass%20on%20its%20cover%20with%20the%20mighty%20Mt%20Harmukh%20looming%20in%20the%20background.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGangbal%20is%20the%20largest%20among%20several%20dozen%20oligotrophic%20lakes%20and%20tarns%20hidden%20in%20the%20alps%20of%20Kashmir%2C%20some%20of%20which%20are%20described%20by%20the%20author%20with%20great%20love%20and%20fondness.%20British%20missionary%20and%20surgeon%20Ernest%20Neve%20remarked%20that%20these%20are%20%E2%80%9Cmost%20impressive%20pieces%20of%20mountain%20scenery%2C%20not%20only%20in%20Kashmir%2C%20but%20in%20the%20world%E2%80%9D.%20Bhattacharji%20says%20Kashmir%20is%20a%20Shangri-la%20%E2%80%9Clavishly%20gifted%20with%20glamour%20and%20beauty%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20other%20chapters%20map%20some%20important%20cultural%20landmarks%2C%20Mughal%20Gardens%20and%20other%20historical%20sites%20in%20Srinagar%20and%20elsewhere%20which%20are%20poignant%20illustrations%20of%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20syncretic%20past%20%E2%80%93%20a%20confluence%20of%20civilisations%20which%20has%20sadly%20turned%20into%20a%20source%20of%20international%20troubles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhattacharji%20writes%2C%20citing%20Charles%20Girdlestone%E2%80%99s%20recherch%C3%A9%20book%20%E2%80%98%3Ci%3EMemorandum%20of%20Cashmere%20and%20Adjacent%20Territories%3C%2Fi%3E%E2%80%99%3A%20%E2%80%9CTurks%20brought%20tea%2C%20silver%20and%20horses%3B%20Chinese%20brought%20earthenware%2C%20shawl%20wool%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98produce%20of%20trans-Himalayan%20looms%E2%80%99%3B%20Baltistanis%20brought%20dry%20fruits%3B%20%E2%80%98Hindustanis%E2%80%99%20brought%20chintzes%2C%20brocades%3B%20Russians%20brought%20guns%2C%20vessels%20and%20tea%20urns.%20They%20took%20away%20pashmina%2C%20iron%2C%20zafran%20and%20rice%20(from%20Kashmir).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBurdened%20by%20a%20bureaucrat%E2%80%99s%20limitations%2C%20Bhattacharji%20believes%20that%20it%20is%20impossible%20to%20describe%20the%20beauty%20of%20Kashmir%20in%20words.%20But%20with%20his%20book%20in%20hand%2C%20one%20can%20experience%20a%20beautiful%20journey%20in%20the%20mind-boggling%20mountains%20cradling%20the%20virgin%20valleys%20of%20Kashmir%20which%20have%20been%20the%20historical%20gateways%20of%20redemption%20and%20solitude%20for%20the%20great%20Sufi%20saints%20and%20scholars%2C%20continent-cruising%20travellers%2C%20inspiration-seeking%20writers%2C%20curious%20surveyors%20and%20occasional%20alpinists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPriced%20at%20Rs%20599%2C%20%3Cem%3EKashmir%20%E2%80%93%20Travels%20in%20Paradise%20on%20Earth%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20must-read%20for%20travellers%20yearning%20for%20a%20tranquil%20few%20days%20away%20from%20the%20chaos%20of%20%E2%80%98civilisation%E2%80%99.%20After%20%E2%80%9