resident%20Manmohan%20Samal%2C%20along%20with%20other%20senior%20leaders%2C%20hinted%20at%20the%20possibility%20of%20the%20BJP%20fielding%20candidates%20in%20all%20147%20assembly%20and%2021%20Lok%20Sabha%20constituencies%20in%20Odisha.%20Mr%20Samal%20stated%20that%20the%20discussions%20in%20Delhi%20were%20solely%20focused%20on%20preparations%20for%20the%20upcoming%20elections%2C%20with%20no%20mention%20of%20an%20alliance%20or%20seat-sharing%20arrangement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20was%20no%20talk%20on%20alliance%20and%20we%20(BJP)%20will%20go%20to%20polls%20alone%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Samal%20said%20as%20quoted%20by%20news%20agency%20PTI.%20%26quot%3BWe%20had%20gone%20to%20Delhi%20to%20hold%20discussions%20with%20the%20central%20leaders%20on%20our%20preparations%20for%20the%20upcoming%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20assembly%20elections%20in%20the%20state.%20No%20talks%20on%20alliance%20or%20seat-sharing%20with%20any%20party%20were%20held%20during%20the%20meeting.%20The%20BJP%20will%20contest%20the%20twin%20polls%20on%20its%20own%20strength.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apparent%20breakdown%20in%20talks%20has%20sparked%20speculations%2C%20especially%20considering%20the%20historical%20context%20of%20the%20BJD's%20departure%20from%20the%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20(NDA)%2015%20years%20ago.%20Former%20BJP%20leader%20and%20minister%20Sushma%20Swaraj%20had%20then%20prophesied%20that%20Naveen%20Patnaik%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20BJD%2C%20would%20%26quot%3Bregret%26quot%3B%20severing%20ties%20after%20an%2011-year%20understanding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ESeat%20Game%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20sources%2C%20the%20alliance%20talks%20hit%20hurdles%20primarily%20over%20seat-sharing%20ratios.%20While%20both%20parties%20had%20initially%20agreed%20on%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20pre-poll%20alliance%2C%20disagreements%20emerged%20over%20the%20distribution%20of%20seats.%20The%20BJD%20sought%20to%20contest%20over%20100%20seats%20in%20the%20147-member%20Odisha%20Assembly%2C%20a%20proposition%20the%20BJP%20found%20unacceptable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConversely%2C%20the%20BJP%20sought%2014%20out%20of%20the%2021%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20in%20Odisha%2C%20a%20demand%20rejected%20by%20the%20BJD.%20The%20stalemate%20over%20seat%20distribution%20escalated%2C%20with%20both%20parties%20remaining%20firm%20on%20their%20respective%20stances.%20In%20the%202019%20general%20elections%2C%20the%20BJD%20had%20secured%2012%20seats%2C%20while%20the%20BJP%20won%20eight%20out%20of%20the%20total%2021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EState%20Unit%20vs%20Central%20Leadership%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOdisha%20BJP%20leaders%2C%20led%20by%20Mr%20Samal%2C%20held%20a%20series%20of%20meetings%20in%20Delhi%20for%20three%20days%2C%20engaging%20with%20central%20leaders%20to%20discuss%20the%20alliance.%20However%2C%20no%20conclusive%20decision%20was%20reached.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20dynamics%20of%20the%20alliance%20talks%20seemed%20to%20have%20shifted%20after%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi's%20visit%20to%20the%20state%20on%20March%205.%20While%20some%20sections%20of%20the%20Odisha%20BJP%20leadership%20are%20reportedly%20are%20on%20board%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20an%20alliance%2C%20others%2C%20including%20Mr%20Samal%2C%20have%20reiterated%20their%20desire%20to%20contest%20the%20polls%20alone.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Samal%20and%20other%20party%20officials%20gathered%20at%20the%20residence%20of%20another%20BJP%20leader%20in%20Bhubaneswar%20last%20night%20for%20further%20discussions.%20The%20BJD's%20VK%20Pandian%20and%20Pranab%20Prakash%20Das%2C%20who%20rushed%20to%20Delhi%20on%20Thursday%20evening%20via%20a%20chartered%20flight%20for%20discussions%20with%20BJP%20central%20leaders%2C%20have%20now%20returned%20to%20the%20state%20capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ESeat%20Ratio%20In%20The%20Past%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20parties%20had%20an%20alliance%20for%20around%2011%20years%20between%201998%20and%202009%2C%20contesting%20three%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20two%20assembly%20elections%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20seat-sharing%20ratio%20in%20their%20previous%20alliances%20was%204%3A3.%20Odisha%20has%20witnessed%20simultaneous%20polls%20since%202004%2C%20with%20a%20consistent%20voting%20pattern%20until%202014%2C%20where%20voters%20typically%20favoured%20the%20BJD%20in%20both%20assembly%20and%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%20However%2C%20the%202019%20elections%20saw%20a%20departure%20from%20this%20trend%2C%20with%20some%20degree%20of%20split%20voting%20observed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202014%20assembly%20elections%2C%20the%20BJD%20secured%20a%20dominant%20position%20with%20117%20out%20of%20147%20seats%2C%20while%20the%20BJP%20won%2010%20and%20the%20Congress%2016.%20The%20projection%20for%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20closely%20mirrored%20the%20outcome%2C%20with%20the%20BJD%20securing%2020%20seats%20and%20the%20BJP%20one.%20In%202019%2C%20a%20shift%20in%20voting%20patterns%20was%20evident%2C%20with%20the%20BJD%20winning%20112%20assembly%20seats%2C%20the%20BJP%2023%2C%20and%20the%20Congress%20nine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Went%20Wrong%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20considered%20the%20BJP's%20most%20reliable%20ally%20in%20the%20NDA%2C%20the%20alliance%20collapsed%20in%202009%20following%20failed%20seat-sharing%20talks.%20The%20breakdown%20was%20officially%20attributed%20to%20the%20BJD's%20demand%20for%20a%20reduction%20in%20the%20BJP's%20share%20of%20assembly%20seats%20from%2063%20to%20around%2040%2C%20and%20parliamentary%20seats%20from%20nine%20to%20six.%20This%20demand%2C%20deemed%20unreasonable%20by%20the%20BJP%20leaders%2C%20led%20to%20the%20withdrawal%20of%20support%20to%20Chief%20Minister%20Naveen%20Patnaik's%20government%2C%20marking%20the%20end%20of%20an%2011-year%20political%20marriage.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20withdrawal%20of%20support%20was%20termed%20by%20BJD%20as%20an%20%26quot%3Bact%20of%20betrayal%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJD-BJP%20pact%20was%20formed%20in%201998%2C%20orchestrated%20by%20senior%20leaders%20Bijay%20Mohapatra%20and%20the%20late%20Pramod%20Mahajan%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709953800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2Fl7a3c4co_naveen-patnaik-pm-modi-_625x300_09_March_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ftalks-with-naveen-patnaiks-party-stall-bjp-eyes-solo-contest-in-odisha-5204331%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20much-anticipated%20pre-poll%20alliance%20and%20seat-sharing%20talks%20between%20Odisha's%20ruling%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%20(BJD)%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20have%20hit%20a%20roadblock%2C%20raising%20the%20prospect%20of%20both%20parties%20contesting%20elections%20solo.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ftalks-with-naveen-patnaiks-party-stall-bjp-eyes-solo-contest-in-odisha-5204331%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Full%20Text%20%7C%20I%20Care%20Very%20Much%20For%20India%2C%20Can't%20Control%20How%20People%20Selectively%20Quote%20Me%3A%20Nitasha%20Kaul%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F08193550%2Fkt-29-feb-b.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWhen%20she%20arrived%20at%20Kempegowda%20airport%20in%20Bengaluru%20on%20February%2023%2C%20Nitasha%20Kaul%20was%20denied%20permission%20to%20enter%20the%20country%20even%20though%20she%20is%20an%20Overseas%20Citizen%20of%20India%20and%20has%20the%20right%20to%20come%20to%20India%20as%20often%20as%20she%20wants.%20She%20was%20given%20no%20explanation%20by%20the%20authorities%20other%20than%20that%20they%20were%20acting%20on%20the%20orders%20of%20the%20government%20in%20Delhi.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EInstead%20she%20was%20held%20in%20detention%2C%20in%20a%20small%20room%2C%20for%20almost%2024%20hours%20before%20being%20sent%20back%20to%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DJBfPhPfzkOI%5C%22%3E35-minute%20interview%20to%20Karan%20Thapar%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Wire%3Cem%3E%2C%20Kaul%2C%20who%20is%20a%20professor%20of%20politics%2C%20international%20relations%20and%20critical%20interdisciplinary%20studies%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Westminster%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20treated%20like%20a%20criminal%2C%E2%80%9D%20adding%20her%20detention%20and%20deportation%20was%20%E2%80%9Cunjust%20and%20unfair%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Ca%20harrowing%20experience%E2%80%9D%20for%20her.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKaul%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Esaid%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20consider%20myself%20Indian%2C%20I%20care%20very%20much%20for%20India%E2%80%9D.%20She%20comprehensively%20responded%20to%20everything%20reported%20by%20the%20%3C%2Fem%3ETimes%20of%20India%3Cem%3E%20and%20NDTV%20as%20explanations%20given%20by%20the%20government%20for%20her%20deportation.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20full%20text%20of%20the%20interview%20is%20provided%20below.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20lightly%20for%20style.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKaran%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cb%3E%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Hello%20and%20welcome%20to%20a%20special%20interview%20for%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20My%20guest%20today%20is%20an%20overseas%20citizen%20of%20India%20(OCI)%2C%20which%20means%20she%20can%20come%20to%20this%20country%20whenever%20she%20wants%3B%20and%20yet%20a%20week%20ago%20on%20February%2023%2C%20when%20she%20arrived%20in%20Bangalore%20to%20attend%20a%20conference%20at%20the%20invitation%20of%20the%20Karnataka%20government%2C%20she%20was%20refused%20entry%20and%20deported%20back%20to%20the%20United%20Kingdom.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJoining%20me%20now%20to%2