uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F9C59%2Fproduction%2F_132852004_oneofthesistersunderburqa-kawoonkhamoosh.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-68500111%230%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Their%20voices%20have%20become%20a%20social%20media%20phenomenon%2C%20protesting%20against%20restrictions%20on%20women%E2%80%99s%20freedoms.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A100%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-68500111%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-68500111.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-68500111.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Better%20Sleep%20Is%20a%20Protective%20Factor%20Against%26nbsp%3BDementia%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F08154912%2Fmatheus-vinicius-kHHwYNA1lnM-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EDementia%20is%20a%20progressive%20loss%20of%20cognitive%20abilities%2C%20such%20as%20memory%2C%20that%20is%20significant%20enough%20to%20have%20an%20impact%20on%20a%20person%E2%80%99s%20daily%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20be%20caused%20by%20a%20number%20of%20different%20diseases%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Falzheimer.ca%2Fen%2Fabout-dementia%2Fwhat-alzheimers-disease%5C%22%3EAlzheimer%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20the%20most%20common%20form.%20Dementia%20is%20caused%20by%20a%20loss%20of%20neurons%20over%20a%20long%20period%20of%20time.%20Since%2C%20by%20the%20time%20symptoms%20appear%2C%20many%20changes%20in%20the%20brain%20have%20already%20occurred%2C%20many%20scientists%20are%20focusing%20on%20studying%20the%20risk%20and%20protective%20factors%20for%20dementia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20risk%20factor%2C%20or%20conversely%2C%20a%20protective%20factor%2C%20is%20a%20condition%20or%20behaviour%20that%20increases%20or%20reduces%20the%20risk%20of%20developing%20a%20disease%2C%20but%20does%20not%20guarantee%20either%20outcome.%20Some%20risk%20factors%20for%20Alzheimer%E2%80%99s%20disease%20and%20dementia%2C%20such%20as%20age%20or%20genetics%2C%20are%20not%20modifiable%2C%20but%20there%20are%20several%20other%20factors%20we%20can%20influence%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Farticle%2FS0140-6736(20)30367-6%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3Especifically%20lifestyle%20habits%20and%20their%20impact%20on%20our%20overall%20health%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20risk%20factors%20include%20depression%2C%20lack%20of%20physical%20activity%2C%20social%20isolation%2C%20high%20blood%20pressure%2C%20obesity%2C%20diabetes%2C%20excessive%20alcohol%20consumption%20and%20smoking%2C%20as%20well%20as%20poor%20sleep.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20been%20focusing%20our%20research%20on%20the%20question%20of%20sleep%20for%20over%2010%20years%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nhlbi.nih.gov%2Fscience%2Fframingham-heart-study-fhs%5C%22%3EFramingham%20Heart%20Study%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20this%20large%20community-based%20cohort%20study%2C%20ongoing%20since%20the%201940s%2C%20the%20health%20of%20surviving%20participants%20has%20been%20monitored%20to%20the%20present%20day.%20As%20researchers%20in%20sleep%20medicine%20and%20epidemiology%2C%20we%20have%20expertise%20in%20researching%20the%20role%20of%20sleep%20and%20sleep%20disorders%20in%20cognitive%20and%20psychiatric%20brain%20ageing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20our%20research%2C%20we%20monitored%20and%20analysed%20the%20sleep%20of%20people%20aged%2060%20and%20over%20to%20see%20who%20did%20%E2%80%94%20or%20did%20not%20%E2%80%94%20develop%20dementia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESleep%20as%20a%20risk%20or%20protective%20factor%20against%20dementia%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESleep%20appears%20to%20play%20an%20essential%20role%20in%20a%20number%20of%20brain%20functions%2C%20such%20as%20memory.%20Good%20quality%20sleep%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamanetwork.com%2Fjournals%2Fjamaneurology%2Ffullarticle%2F2793873%5C%22%3Ecould%20therefore%20play%20a%20vital%20role%20in%20preventing%20dementia%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESleep%20is%20important%20for%20maintaining%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fscience.1241224%5C%22%3Egood%20connections%20in%20the%20brain%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Recently%2C%20research%20has%20revealed%20that%20sleep%20seems%20to%20have%20a%20function%20similar%20to%20that%20of%20a%20garbage%20truck%20for%20the%20brain%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1016%2Fj.mad.2023.111899%5C%22%3Edeep%20sleep%20could%20be%20crucial%20for%20eliminating%20metabolic%20waste%20from%20the%20brain%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20clearing%20certain%20proteins%2C%20such%20as%20those%20known%20to%20accumulate%20in%20the%20brains%20of%20people%20with%20Alzheimer%E2%80%99s%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20links%20between%20deep%20sleep%20and%20dementia%20still%20have%20to%20be%20clarified.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20deep%20sleep%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20a%20night%E2%80%99s%20sleep%2C%20we%20go%20through%20several%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fceams-carsm.ca%2Fen%2Fa-propos-du-sommeil%2F%5C%22%3Esleep%20stages%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20succeed%20one%20another%20and%20are%20repeated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENREM%20sleep%20(non-rapid%20eye%20movement%20sleep)%20is%20divided%20into%20light%20NREM%20sleep%20(NREM1%20stage)%2C%20NREM%20sleep%20(NREM2%20stage)%20and%20deep%20NREM%20sleep%2C%20also%20called%20slow-wave%20sleep%20(NREM3%20stage).%20The%20latter%20is%20associated%20with%20several%20restorative%20functions.%20Next%2C%20REM%20sleep%20(rapid%20eye%20movement%20sleep)%20is%20the%20stage%20generally%20associated%20with%20the%20most%20vivid%20dreams.%20An%20adult%20generally%20spends%20around%2015%20to%2020%20per%20cent%20of%20each%20night%20in%20deep%20sleep%2C%20if%20we%20add%20up%20all%20the%20periods%20of%20NREM3%20sleep.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20sleep%20changes%20are%20common%20in%20adults%2C%20such%20as%20going%20to%20bed%20and%20waking%20up%20earlier%2C%20sleeping%20for%20shorter%20periods%20of%20time%20and%20less%20deeply%2C%20and%20waking%20up%20more%20frequently%20during%20the%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(min-width%3A%201466px)%20754px%2C%20(max-width%3A%20599px)%20100vw%2C%20(min-width%3A%20600px)%20600px%2C%20237px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F579041%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240229-16-efo9mx.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26q%3D45%26auto%3Dformat%26w%3D754%26fit%3Dclip%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F579041%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240229-16-efo9mx.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D45%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D279%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D1%20600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F579041%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240229-16-efo9mx.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D30%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D279%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D2%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F579041%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240229-16-efo9mx.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D15%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D279%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D3%201800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F579041%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240229-16-efo9mx.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D45%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D350%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D1%20754w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F579041%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240229-16-efo9mx.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D30%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D350%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D2%201508w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F579041%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240229-16-efo9mx.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D15%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D350%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D3%202262w%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22279%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESleep%20stages%2C%20and%20the%20role%20of%20deep%20sleep%20for%20brain%20health.%20Credit%3A%20Andr%C3%A9e-Ann%20Baril%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELoss%20of%20deep%20sleep%20linked%20to%20dementia%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParticipants%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamanetwork.com%2Fjournals%2Fjamaneurology%2Ffullarticle%2F2810957%5C%22%3EFramingham%20Heart%20Study%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20assessed%20using%20a%20sleep%20recording%20%E2%80%94%20known%20as%20polysomnography%20%E2%80%94%20on%20two%20occasions%2C%20approximately%20five%20years%20apart%2C%20in%201995-1998%20and%20again%20in%202001-2003.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20showed%20a%20reduction%20in%20their%20deep%20slow-wave%20sleep%20over%20the%20years%2C%20as%20is%20to%20be%20expected%20with%20ageing.%20Conversely%2C%20the%20amount%20of%20deep%20sleep%20in%20some%20people%20remained%20stable%20or%20even%20increased.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20team%20of%20researchers%20from%20the%20Framingham%20Heart%20Study%20followed%20346%20participants%20aged%2060%20and%20over%20for%20a%20further%2017%20years%20to%20observe%20who%20developed%20dementia%20and%20who%20did%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProgressive%20loss%20of%20deep%20sleep%20over%20time%20was%20associated%20with%20an%20increased%20risk%20of%20dementia%2C%20whatever%20the%20cause%2C%20and%20particularly%20Alzheimer%E2%80%99s%20type%20dementia.%20These%20results%20were%20independent%20of%20many%20other%20risk%20factors%20for%20dementia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20our%20results%20do%20not%20prove%20that%20loss%20of%20deep%20sleep%20causes%20dementia%2C%20they%20do%20suggest%20that%20it%20could%20be%20a%20risk%20factor%20in%20the%20elderly.%20Other%20aspects%20of%20sleep%20may%20also%20be%20important%2C%20such%20as%20its%20duration%20and%20quality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStrategies%20to%20improve%20deep%20sleep%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKnowing%20the%20impact%20of%20a%20lack%20of%20deep%20sleep%20on%20cognitive%20health%2C%20what%20strategies%20can%20be%20used%20to%20improve%20it%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%20and%20foremost%2C%20if%20you%E2%80%99re%20experiencing%20sleep%20problems%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20worth%20talking%20to%20your%20doctor.%20Many%20sleep%20disorders%20are%20underdiagnosed%20and%20treatable%2C%20particularly%20through%20behavioural%20(i.e.%20non-medicinal)%20approaches.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdopting%20good%20sleep%20habits%20can%20help%2C%20such%20as%20going%20to%20bed%20and%20getting%20up%20at%20consistent%20times%20or%20avoiding%20bright%20or%20blue%20light%20in%20bed%2C%20like%20that%20of%20screens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20also%20avoid%20caffeine%2C%20limit%20your%20alcohol%20intake%2C%20maintain%20a%20healthy%20weight%2C%20be%20physically%20active%20during%20the%20day%2C%20and%20sleep%20in%20a%20comfortable%2C%20dark%20and%20quiet%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20role%20of%20deep%20sleep%20in%20preventing%20dementia%20remains%20to%20be%20explored%20and%20studied.%20Encouraging%20sleep%20with%20good%20lifestyle%20habits%20could%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20help%20us%20age%20in%20a%20healthier%20way.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F222854%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAndr%C3%A9e-Ann%20Baril%20is%C2%A0Professeure-chercheure%20adjointe%20au%20D%C3%A9partement%20de%20m%C3%A9decine%2C%20Universit%C3%A9%20de%20Montr%C3%A9al%20and%20Matthew%20Pase%20is%C2%A0Associate%20Professor%20of%20Neurology%20and%20Epidemiology%2C%20Monash%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%